node_6.subject: Klaus Mueller
node_6.description: This is Klaus Mueller's plan for Monday February 13: wake up and complete the morning routine at 7:00 am, head to the library at Oak Hill College at 8:00 am, spend the day writing his research paper on gentrification, take a break and have lunch at Hobbs Cafe around 12:00 pm, continue working on his research paper until around 4:00 pm, head home and have dinner at 5:00 pm, spend the evening relaxing and possibly watching TV or reading.
